<TITLE> Court orders arrest of Abu Zafar Chowdhury </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Sunday ordered police to arrest chairman of Mercantile Cooperative Bank Ltd Abu Zafar Chowdhury who faces charges of hiding illegal assets. Dhaka metropolitan sessions judge NM Bashir Ullah ordered police to submit a report on whether the Chowdhury was arrested or not on May 31, assistant sheristadar of the court Nurul Alam told bdnews24.com. The Anticorruption Commission filed a case with Ramna Police Station against Chowdhury on Oct 29, 2009 for acquiring illegal assets worth nearly Tk 2. 25 crore and concealing information of the wealth. ACC deputy director Mohammad Fanafillah pressed charges with Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court on Apr 28. Chowdhury faces another 15 cases of fraud and embezzlement of funds. Vice chairman of the bank, Zaki Uddin Ahmed said he filed five cases with Gulshan Police Station against Chowdhury in 2004, 2005 and this year for forgery and misappropriation of money. In one of the cases his wife and in another his brother have been made accused. b
